<document xmlns="http://cnx.rice.edu/cnxml" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML">
<title>Lotubundnir eiginleikar</title>
<metadata xmlns:md="http://cnx.rice.edu/mdml">
  <md:content-id>m68829</md:content-id>
  <md:title>Lotubundnir eiginleikar</md:title>
  <md:abstract><para id="para-00001">Í lok þessa kafla muntu geta:</para><list id="list-00001"><item>Flokkað frumefni</item><item>Spáð fyrir um lotubundna eiginleika aðalflokka frumefna</item></list></md:abstract>
  <md:uuid>f7224d2a-76cb-49f8-91ba-915271b912af</md:uuid>
</metadata>

<content>
<para id="fs-idp221982176">Við hefjum þennan kafla á því að skoða hegðun aðalflokkamálma í tengslum við stöðu þeirra í lotukerfinu. Megináhersla þessa kafla verður á hagnýtingu lotubundinna eiginleika á aðalflokkamálma.</para>
<para id="fs-idp149998640">Hægt er að skipta frumefnum í hópa eftir rafeindaskipan þeirra. <term id="term-00001">Aðalflokka frumefni (e. representative elements)</term> eru frumefni þar sem <emphasis effect="italics">s</emphasis>- og <emphasis effect="italics">p</emphasis>-svigrúm eru að fyllast. Hliðarmálmar eru frumefni þar sem <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis>-svigrúm (hópar 3–11 í lotukerfinu) eru að fyllast og innri hliðarmálmar eru frumefni þar sem <emphasis effect="italics">f</emphasis>-svigrúm eru að fyllast. <emphasis effect="italics">d</emphasis>-svigrúmin fyllast með frumefnunum í hóp 11; þess vegna teljast frumefnin í hóp 12 til aðalflokka frumefna því síðasta rafeindin fer á <emphasis effect="italics">s</emphasis>-svigrúm. Málmar meðal aðalflokka frumefna eru <term id="term-00002">aðalflokkamálmar (e. representative metals)</term>. Málmkenndir eiginleikar stafa af getu frumefnis til að tapa ytri gildisrafeindum sínum og leiða meðal annars til mikillar varma- og rafleiðni, auk annarra eðlis- og efnaeiginleika. Það eru 20 ógeislavirkir aðalflokkamálmar í hópum 1, 2, 3, 12, 13, 14 og 15 í lotukerfinu (frumefnin sem eru skyggð gul á <link target-id="CNX_Chem_18_01_PeriodicPU3"/>). Geislavirku frumefnin kópernikíum, fleróvíum, pólon og lifermoríum eru einnig málmar en eru utan gildissviðs þessa kafla.</para>
<figure id="CNX_Chem_18_01_PeriodicPU3"><media id="fs-idp101665920" alt="The Periodic Table of Elements is shown. The 18 columns are labeled “Group” and the 7 rows are labeled “Period.” Below the table to the right is a box labeled “Color Code” with different colors for representative metals, transition and inner transition metals, radioactive elements, metalloids, and nonmetals, as well as solids, liquids, and gases. Each element will be described in this order: atomic number; name; symbol; whether it is a representative metal, transition and inner transition metal, radioactive element, metalloid, or nonmetal; whether it is a solid, liquid, or gas; and atomic mass. Beginning at the top left of the table, or period 1, group 1, is a box containing “1; hydrogen; H; nonmetal; gas; and 1.008.” There is only one other element box in period 1, group 18, which contains “2; helium; H e; nonmetal; gas; and 4.003.” Period 2, group 1 contains “3; lithium; L i; representative metal; solid; and 6.94” Group 2 contains “4; beryllium; B e; representative metal; solid; and 9.012.” Groups 3 through 12 are skipped and group 13 contains “5; boron; B; metalloid; solid; 10.81.” Group 14 contains “6; carbon; C; nonmetal; solid; and 12.01.” Group 15 contains “7; nitrogen; N; nonmetal; gas; and 14.01.” Group 16 contains “8; oxygen; O; nonmetal; gas; and 16.00.” Group 17 contains “9; fluorine; F; nonmetal; gas; and 19.00.” Group 18 contains “10; neon; N e; nonmetal; gas; and 20.18.” Period 3, group 1 contains “11; sodium; N a; representative metal; solid; and 22.99.” Group 2 contains “12; magnesium; M g; representative metal; solid; and 24.31.” Groups 3 through 12 are skipped again in period 3 and group 13 contains “13; aluminum; A l; representative metal; solid; and 26.98.” Group 14 contains “14; silicon; S i; metalloid; solid; and 28.09.” Group 15 contains “15; phosphorous; P; nonmetal; solid; and 30.97.” Group 16 contains “16; sulfur; S; nonmetal; solid; and 32.06.” Group 17 contains “17;